  "translations": {
    "en": "As for your property's right, take only from the lawful, spend only in the proper. Do not prefer over yourself those who will not praise you. Act in obedience to your Lord, do not be miserly lest you fall into regret. There is no strength save in Allah. As for the creditor's right, if you have means give him; if in hardship, satisfy with good words and send away gently. The associate's right is not to deceive, cheat, or trick him, and fear Allah in his affair.",
